Which would be reasons for modifying a hierarchy that was previously created using the
Hierarchy wizard? (Choose two)
A. To add an attribute to a hierarchy level.
B. To add a measure element to the hierarchy.
C. To specify a fact build for the hierarchy.
D. To add a level to the hierarchy.
E. To specify a metadata dimension for the hierarchy.
F. To add a derived dimension element to the hierarchy.
Answer: A,D

A. Disable dimension breaking on the fact build.
B. Disable fact build logging.
C. Enable dimension breaking on the fact build.
D. Enable auditing on the fact build.
